09:10.139 --> 09:12.208
So,

09:12.241 --> 09:16.980
10 to 12 million people regularly
attend home churches in America.

09:17.013 --> 09:18.382
What do you think accounts
for that?

09:20.283 --> 09:22.485
Well, I think that there's a lot
of people that attend church

09:22.519 --> 09:27.258
because they can remain unnoticed,
they blend in with the big crowds.

09:28.390 --> 09:32.495
But that's not how God intends
His relationship with us to be.

09:32.528 --> 09:34.965
You see, going to church
is a very social activity

09:34.998 --> 09:38.836
and your bond with your fellow
believers is incredibly important.

09:38.869 --> 09:43.307
And here at Emeth,
it's our goal to foster

09:43.340 --> 09:47.076
that relationship between
God and His followers,

09:47.110 --> 09:49.846
and to help them grow
in their walk with Christ.

09:49.879 --> 09:51.915
You see there's strength
in numbers.

09:53.350 --> 09:58.822
Speaking of numbers, this very small
town already has a Catholic church,

09:58.855 --> 10:01.024
a Methodist church,
a Baptist church

10:01.057 --> 10:04.293
and even a non-denominational church
that meets at the Petersons house

10:04.326 --> 10:08.798
and gets out just in time for everyone
to make it to the farmers' market.

10:08.831 --> 10:13.770
Everyone here is pretty set in their ways and
anything new doesn't tend to last very long.

10:14.837 --> 10:16.973
What makes Emeth so special?

10:19.241 --> 10:23.980
Father used to tell us a story
about an old western town.

10:24.014 --> 10:26.917
It's hot there,
it's hotter even than here,

10:27.951 --> 10:31.522
and everybody was always looking for
different ways to quench their thirst.

10:31.554 --> 10:34.157
They tried tonics and powders
and what have you not,

10:34.191 --> 10:38.461
but nothing ever left them
completely satisfied.

10:38.495 --> 10:40.397
And then one day
a man came along

10:40.429 --> 10:45.235
and he built them a well.
Water, real thing.

10:46.336 --> 10:50.307
See, Miss Cutler, when... when when you give
people what they've always been wanting,

10:51.575 --> 10:54.078
they'll never need
anything else.

10:56.245 --> 11:00.350
So you've come to our little
western town to bring us Emeth?

11:00.383 --> 11:03.320
- Heh. I mean, if you want to put it that way.
- I don't.

11:03.352 --> 11:06.790
- So your religious organization...
- It's a church.

11:08.424 --> 11:13.996
It's been in the news many times for
its controversial views and practices.

11:14.029 --> 11:15.399
Should we go over
a few of those...

11:15.432 --> 11:17.835
Look, I know
where you're going with that

11:17.868 --> 11:20.871
and those are very extreme cases and
Emeth has dealt with them accordingly.

11:20.903 --> 11:23.206
- Heh. But you haven't...
- Next question.

11:26.876 --> 11:30.246
How does it feel having a woman
asking questions in your church?

11:30.279 --> 11:32.515
Excuse me?

11:32.548 --> 11:34.550
