with you.

24:32.260 --> 24:36.332
The strange thing is though I'll still
apologize profusely when I get back.

24:38.299 --> 24:41.370
Do you really feel like
you're doing something wrong?

24:41.403 --> 24:43.073
Logically no.

24:44.039 --> 24:46.076
But like guilt just comes
with the territory.

24:48.044 --> 24:51.781
Every little thing I do, it's
this feeling that I can't shake,

24:52.815 --> 24:55.151
which sucks
'cause sex is awesome.

24:57.787 --> 24:59.855
Yeah, how do you reconcile that?

25:02.825 --> 25:03.860
I can't.

25:09.097 --> 25:12.167
But if there is a God,

25:12.201 --> 25:15.371
He's a lot more loving and
open-minded than Emeth preaches.

25:15.403 --> 25:20.041
I mean, there's got to be more than
one way to live your life, right?

25:24.113 --> 25:29.251
I mean,
why should someone perish

25:29.285 --> 25:32.689
just because they lived a life
different from everyone else.

25:34.089 --> 25:37.759
I wish I could be more like you.
More definitive.

25:37.792 --> 25:41.030
That I could just write it all
off without a second thought.

25:42.097 --> 25:46.403
You know, I used to buy into the
whole thing too when I was young.

25:48.436 --> 25:52.040
But when I was in third grade,
this boy in my church,

25:52.074 --> 25:54.009
he was just a few years older
than me,

25:54.943 --> 25:57.946
said that the priest
had touched him, yeah.

25:57.980 --> 26:00.182
And then a bunch of other kids,
boys and girls,

26:00.215 --> 26:03.318
came out and said that he had
done the same thing to them.

26:04.420 --> 26:07.023
You know what the church did?

26:07.056 --> 26:12.194
They moved him to another
church, heh, like an hour away.

26:15.897 --> 26:19.301
One of the boys killed himself
a few years later

26:19.335 --> 26:23.440
and still nothing happened
to that priest.

26:27.143 --> 26:29.778
And this isn't
a unique situation.

26:29.811 --> 26:33.082
That wasn't one bad guy
doing a bad thing.

26:34.182 --> 26:35.785
And the church was complicit.

26:35.817 --> 26:41.223
And so, as part of the church,
I was complicit.

26:41.257 --> 26:44.494
When I told my parents that,
they kicked me out.

26:47.563 --> 26:50.166
I've been making my own way
ever since.

26:51.267 --> 26:53.303
That's why I like
coming out here.

26:54.470 --> 26:55.872
Why is that?

26:55.904 --> 26:58.840
'Cause life is chaos,

26:58.874 --> 27:02.478
but you can choose to
just walk out into that water,

27:02.510 --> 27:06.816
close your eyes
and see what happens.

27:10.686 --> 27:14.556
There's something freeing
about giving it into the chaos

27:14.589 --> 27:17.526
and coming out on top...

27:19.461 --> 27:20.864
if you're lucky.

27:24.333 --> 27:25.902
And if you're not?

27:27.001 --> 27:27.936
Then you're not.

27:31.941 --> 27:32.842
-Yeah.

27:34.276 --> 27:36.144
- It made so much sense though.
- Oh, yeah?

27:36.178 --> 27:37.914
- Yeah.
- Maybe to you.

27:39.882 --> 27:41.284
- I didn't mean it like that, heh.
- Oh, okay.

27:41.317 --> 27:43.152
Okay, maybe a little.

27:43.184 --> 27:45.053
Are you sure
I can't give you a ride home?

27:45.086 --> 27:47.824
No, I'm fine.
I prefer walking.

27:47.856 --> 27:50.192
Gives me time to clear my head
and practice my apology.

27:50.226 --> 27:54.096
- Are you gonna go home?
- I have to, eventually.

27:54.128 --> 27:55.964
Hmm, tsk.

27:55.998 --> 27:59.335
Well, do you want to come
in this time?

28:05.374 --> 28:07.076
No cameras in here.

28:15.584 --> 28:18.554
Can I maybe get
you a drink or something?

29:04.333 --> 29:06.502
- Hey.
- Hey.

29:06.535 --> 29:09.939
- You want some breakfast?
- Sure.

29:13.174 --> 29:15.211
So I'm gonna warn you,

29:15.243 --> 29:18.013
there might not be anything
edible in my fridge, like at all.

29:18.047 --> 29:19.915
- Nothing...
- Morning.

29:22.651 --> 29:27.089
Don't you two make
a nice couple? Mighty nice.

29:27.122 --> 29:28.658
What the fuck
are you doing here?

29:28.691 --> 29:31.192
Get out.

29:31.226 --> 29:35.565
Excuse me.
You never changed your locks.

29:36.965 --> 29:38.667
You never even asked
for my keys,

29:38.701 --> 29:42.939
so you must have wanted me to
come back through those doors.

29:42.971 --> 29:45.574
Get the fuck out!

29:45.606 --> 29:46.942
Shh.

29:49.545 --> 29:52.382
Aren't you gonna introduce me
to your new friend?

29:54.415 --> 29:56.484
I knew you'd move on

29:56.518 --> 30:01.290
but I had hoped you would be with
someone who wasn't so beautiful.

30:05.059 --> 30:06.194
It's time for you to go.

30:07.628 --> 30:08.696
That's funny

30:10.231 --> 30:15.070
'cause, uh, I was thinking
the same thing about you.

30:15.104 --> 30:16.439
Boys.

30:16.471 --> 30:18.139
Seth, do not do this please,
I beg you.

30:18.173 --> 30:19.541
- Hey, hey.
- What the... Hey! Hey!

30:19.575 --> 30:22.111
- Thomas! Thomas!
- You son of a bitch!

30:22.144 --> 30:24.547
Fuck you! Fuck you!

30:27.750 --> 30:29.751
Stop it.

30:36.557 --> 30:38.626
You know,
I never could figure out

30:38.660 --> 30:42.365
what I had to do to make you see
that we were perfect for each other.

30:42.397 --> 30:44.699
Why can't you just see that?

30:49.605 --> 30:52.607
Hey, boss,
what do you want us to do with him?

30:57.112 --> 30:59.215
Take him back where he belongs.

31:09.090 --> 31:10.726
Jessica.

31:13.528 --> 31:14.663
Jessica.

31:30.412 --> 31:35.151
So,
you want to tell us where you've been?

31:37.553 --> 31:39.288
Look, we already know.
Just own up to it.

31:39.320 --> 31:41.256
Hold your tongue.

31:44.425 --> 31:47.329
You spent the night
with another.

31:48.363 --> 31:50.298
You're weak in the eyes of God

31:50.332 --> 31:52.701
and you have soiled your
relationship with your betrothed.

31:52.733 --> 31:55.103
She's not my betrothed.

31:56.238 --> 31:58.041
Never agreed to that.

32:06.815 --> 32:08.683
It's about time somebody around here
started thinking for themselves.

32:08.717 --> 32:11.320
Sit down.

32:12.554 --> 32:16.525
You think you can break God's
rules and just get away with it?

32:16.557 --> 32:18.827
Haven't I taught you
better than that by now?

32:20.761 --> 32:24.332
Yeah, sure.

32:26.201 --> 32:28.671
All right.
Let's talk about God's rules.

32:32.441 --> 32:35.845
That book says we can't
have bacon or shrimp.

32:35.877 --> 32:39.781
You can't trim your beard.
No mixing meat or dairy.

32:39.815 --> 32:43.352
So I guess we're all going to hell for
eating fucking cheeseburgers, right?

32:43.384 --> 32:44.752
No sex.

32:44.787 --> 32:47.390
But you turn a blind eye if it's
the woman you want me to marry.

32:49.290 --> 32:53.162
How exactly do you choose which
of God's rules we follow, Father?

32:55.263 --> 32:58.366
- If only your mother were...
- No.

32:58.400 --> 32:59.634
No, you don't get to do that.

32:59.667 --> 33:02.504
My mother?
I never knew my mother.

33:02.538 --> 33:04.673
You've never had a wife.

33:04.705 --> 33:06.841
Are the three of us
even related?

33:06.875 --> 33:09.678
Oh, right, I forgot, we're not
allowed to ask about that.

33:09.711 --> 33:12.381
We're not allowed to ask any fucking
questions about anything at all.

33:14.316 --> 33:17.819
So, no, you don't get
to guilt-trip me for shit.

33:17.853 --> 33:21.757
You don't have to stand there like I'm a
sinner when you're nothing but a hypocrite.

33:24.326 --> 33:25.528
Repent.

33:29.730 --> 33:30.866
Or what?

33:34.903 --> 33:36.739
That's what I thought.

33:38.272 --> 33:39.641
I'll show myself out.

33:53.488 --> 33:55.191
Here's your water.

33:55.223 --> 33:59.227
I have to go to work but
mom's here if you need anything.

33:59.260 --> 34:02.330
Oh, and your phone was ringing,
I think you missed a call.

34:10.371 --> 34:11.873
Are you okay?

34:37.965 --> 34:39.568
Exactly where I wanna be.

34:40.969 --> 34:42.605
I love you.

34:43.704 --> 34:45.340
And I love you.

35:20.775 --> 35:22.244
Mama!

35:23.378 --> 35:24.547
You awake?

35:27.581 --> 35:29.018
Mama!

35:53.675 --> 35:54.977
It's okay.

35:55.010 --> 35:57.713
- She's gone.
- I know. I know.

35:59.014 --> 36:00.548
Okay.

36:00.581 --> 36:02.518
- She's gone.
- I know.

36:16.664 --> 36:18.833
This isn't the same room
anymore.

36:21.670 --> 36:24.505
I've known this room
my entire life.

36:26.375 --> 36:30.679
I've slept in here,
played games in here.

36:32.481 --> 36:34.350
I even brought some boys in here

36:34.382 --> 36:36.785
because the bed
was so much nicer than mine.

36:39.887 --> 36:42.724
Now everything is gone.

36:46.027 --> 36:47.630
It's just empty.

36:53.969 --> 36:56.371
Whom I gonna take care of now?

36:57.806 --> 37:00.742
Who's gonna take care of me?
I'm not like you.

37:00.775 --> 37:05.580
I'm not self-motivated.
I'm not good at being alone.

37:05.614 --> 37:07.983
You're stronger than you think.

37:08.016 --> 37:10.952
What am I supposed to do now,
just throw myself into my work?

37:10.985 --> 37:12.987
Where's my bright outlook
in that?

37:21.429 --> 37:22.565
You'll figure it out.

37:23.864 --> 37:26.401
I wish you could just tell me
what to do.

37:26.434 --> 37:27.735
The girl with all the answers.

37:29.137 --> 37:32.408
I know.
I wish I could too.

37:39.146 --> 37:41.083
I'm happy it was peaceful.

37:42.516 --> 37:44.986
I'm happy she was asleep
when it happened.

37:51.159 --> 37:53.996
I know it's not gonna
go back to being the same,

37:56.164 --> 37:58.134
but is it ever gonna be
anything?

38:02.170 --> 38:04.072
You'll figure it out.

38:04.105 --> 38:08.177
One day you'll wake up
and it won't hurt as bad,

38:08.210 --> 38:11.679
and it won't be so lonely.

38:11.713 --> 38:13.516
You'll go in that new direction.

38:53.121 --> 38:54.757
Tell me the plan again.

38:59.860 --> 39:02.230
We'll have a little baby girl

39:03.597 --> 39:08.770
and she will be the most beautiful
thing that you or I have ever seen.

39:10.137 --> 39:13.842
I'll go back as assistant editor
of the paper.

39:13.875 --> 39:17.213
You can stay home with our daughter
while writing your stories.

39:19.146 --> 39:22.518
By the time
our little girl turns six,

39:22.550 --> 39:28.023
we will be in a city too big for
small-minded people to hurt us.

39:31.592 --> 39:35.563
She'll grow up
and be who she wants to be,

39:36.264 --> 39:38.934
believe what she wants
to believe,

39:39.934 --> 39:42.505
and love who she wants to love.

39:43.838 --> 39:49.010
No one will ever tell her that she
is less than or not good enough.

39:52.280 --> 39:56.919
She'll have a life far better
than you or I could ever imagine.

39:58.719 --> 40:02.023
And then you and I will grow old
and wrinkly together,

40:04.159 --> 40:08.163
bound together by a closeness
that no poet could put into words

40:08.195 --> 40:10.632
and no scientist
could ever explain.

40:15.670 --> 40:18.139
- I love you.
- I love you.

40:20.842 --> 40:24.680
<i>♪ Away in a manger ♪</i>

40:24.713 --> 40:27.983
<i>♪ No crib for a bed ♪</i>

40:28.016 --> 40:32.753
<i>♪ The little Lord Jesus
Lay down ♪</i>

40:32.786 --> 40:34.789
<i>♪ His sweet head ♪</i>

40:34.822 --> 40:38.659
<i>♪ The stars in the sky ♪</i>

40:38.693 --> 40:41.730
<i>♪ Look down where he lay ♪</i>

41:08.322 --> 41:10.692
Hi, Thomas.
Hi, Jessica.

41:10.724 --> 41:12.661
- Hello.
- Hi.

41:12.693 --> 41:15.396
Jessica, you look incredible.

41:15.429 --> 41:18.766
I've never seen a more beautiful
pregnant person before.

41:18.800 --> 41:20.002
Thank you.

41:22.170 --> 41:24.840
I know it's early but,

41:24.873 --> 41:28.744
ah,
we got you a Christmas present.

41:28.777 --> 41:30.778
It's baby blankets.

41:30.811 --> 41:34.415
Uh, Michael actually picked them out.
I just wrapped them.

41:34.449 --> 41:36.952
Thank You, Georgine,
that's very kind of you.

41:36.985 --> 41:39.355
Ah. I hope the child
enjoys them.

41:40.255 --> 41:46.228
And I wanted to let you both know that
Michael and I will be getting married

41:46.260 --> 41:48.029
the weekend
after Christmas.

41:49.731 --> 41:53.335
Anyway, I would love
if you both could make it out.

41:53.367 --> 41:56.237
It will be at Emeth
starting at 4:30.

41:56.271 --> 42:00.307
And I know Michael would be
really happy to see you there too.

42:00.340 --> 42:02.943
Yeah, we'll...
we'll check our calendar.

42:02.976 --> 42:08.215
Great.
Well, happy holidays, heh!

42:08.248 --> 42:10.384
- Merry Christmas.
- Bye.

42:20.027 --> 42:23.764
- At some point I'm probably gonna have to pee.
- Mm-hm.

42:23.797 --> 42:25.967
Do you think it's safe to go
in there at this time?

42:27.135 --> 42:31.006
Why, did you want the Emeth VIP
bathroom experience?

42:31.039 --> 42:32.908
Yes. Yes, I do.

42:32.940 --> 42:34.175
We'll find a way to make
that happen.

42:34.208 --> 42:38.413
Is that a promise? Good.

42:38.445 --> 42:39.980
- Hold me to it.
- I will.

42:40.014 --> 42:41.216
- Okay.
- Heh.

42:46.920 --> 42:48.056
Hi there.

42:50.190 --> 42:53.427
- Hi there.
- She's really pregnant.

42:53.460 --> 42:55.796
- Yes, she is.
- I am.

42:55.829 --> 42:58.266
- When's she due?
- Next month.

42:58.298 --> 43:00.134
You're not wearing
a wedding ring.

43:00.168 --> 43:02.370
That's because
we're not married.

43:02.402 --> 43:06.741
Oh, poor child.

43:10.311 --> 43:11.814
Enjoy the wedding.

43:17.085 --> 43:21.757
I love you, Michael, and
I know that you love me too.

43:21.789 --> 43:26.260
Because of this,
I desire to be your wife, heh.

43:26.293 --> 43:31.866
For 20 years I have prayed that
God would lead me to His choice

43:31.900 --> 43:38.039
and I am confident His will
is being fulfilled tonight.

43:38.072 --> 43:42.844
Through the pressures of the present
and the uncertainties of the future,

43:42.876 --> 43:45.480
I promise to be faithful to you.

43:45.512 --> 43:50.985
I will love, serve, and obey you
as long as we both are alive.

43:51.018 --> 43:55.089
Christ told us, "The wife should
submit herself to her own husband

43:55.123 --> 43:58.960
as to the Lord for as Christ
is head of the church,

43:58.992 --> 44:01.028
so is the husband
head of his wife."

44:02.297 --> 44:05.900
Michael,
I submit myself to you.

44:14.909 --> 44:19.981
Georgine, I love you,
and I know that God has ordained our love.

44:20.949 --> 44:25.052
Because of that,
I desire to be your husband.

44:25.085 --> 44:29.456
Together we will be vessels
for His service

44:29.489 --> 44:32.126
in accordance with His plan

44:32.159 --> 44:36.864
so that in all areas of our life,
Christ will have preeminence.

44:38.365 --> 44:40.434
Through the pressures
of the present

44:40.467 --> 44:45.105
and the uncertainty of the future,
I promise to be faithful to you.

44:45.139 --> 44:48.943
I promise to love you,
to guide you

44:48.976 --> 44:54.516
and to protect you as Christ did for
His church as long as we're both alive.

44:55.916 --> 45:00.521
According to Ephesians 5 and
the power enabled through him,

45:01.521 --> 45:06.929
I promise to love you as Christ loved
the church so much that He died for her.

45:08.061 --> 45:13.335
And I will treat you as part of me
because in His sight we will be one.

45:24.512 --> 45:29.117
I now pronounce you
man and wife.

45:34.088 --> 45:39.294
Ladies and gentlemen,
Mr. and Mrs. Hallback.

45:58.445 --> 46:00.181
Hello, ladies.

46:01.282 --> 46:05.287
Wow, look at you.

46:05.320 --> 46:07.189
Isn't this just beautiful?

46:08.655 --> 46:11.492
A divine miracle.

46:11.525 --> 46:14.629
Oh, isn't this just beautiful?

46:15.596 --> 46:18.266
That's enough.
Jess, you all right?

46:18.298 --> 46:24.038
- Yeah, I'm... I'm... I'm fine.
- Try not to make a scene now, boy.

46:24.072 --> 46:26.974
Not on such
a beautiful occasion.

46:27.007 --> 46:29.009
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

46:29.043 --> 46:31.613
He's a very dedicated
and passionate follower.

46:31.646 --> 46:33.315
Emeth is lucky to have him.

46:34.449 --> 46:35.983
He's an abusive creep.

46:36.016 --> 46:38.619
- He who repents...
- Yeah, save it.

46:38.652 --> 46:40.454
Jess, why don't we go back
to the reception?

46:40.487 --> 46:44.960
Oh, the reception
is for members only,

46:44.992 --> 46:49.096
not for the unwholesome,
not for sinners

46:49.130 --> 46:53.101
who shamelessly lure their
adultery in front of others.

46:55.202 --> 46:59.340
You've made your choice.
There's no reason to come back.

47:09.583 --> 47:11.685
I never wanted a wedding.

47:11.719 --> 47:14.688
When I was growing up, all the girls
would talk about their special day

47:14.722 --> 47:17.592
and I just couldn't picture it
for myself.

47:17.625 --> 47:19.994
I dreaded it.

47:20.027 --> 47:23.163
I had nightmares about standing next
to someone I had no connection with.

47:23.197 --> 47:27.235
- And now?
- Now I'm in love.

47:27.268 --> 47:30.472
I don't need rings
or sexist vows.

47:30.505 --> 47:34.142
I'm here.
I'm never going anywhere.

47:35.742 --> 47:39.413
- I love you.
- I love you too.

47:39.447 --> 47:41.516
- Let's get the hell out of here, heh.
- Yes, ma'am.

48:38.306 --> 48:40.675
All right, Jessica,
get your ass out of here.

48:40.708 --> 48:43.144
You said you were leaving
at 3:00 today, it's 3:30.

48:43.844 --> 48:46.180
Shit, okay.

48:46.213 --> 48:49.717
Um, I'm almost done marking Lisa's
story and then I am out of here.

48:49.750 --> 48:50.818
Good.

48:56.324 --> 48:58.760
Dani, oh, my God,
what happened?

48:58.793 --> 49:02.329
Oh, this? What, you don't like
my new beauty marks?

49:02.362 --> 49:05.232
Dani, what happened?

49:05.266 --> 49:08.369
A few of your church friends
paid me a visit last night.

49:08.402 --> 49:10.405
They threw rocks and bricks
through my window.

49:10.438 --> 49:12.307
Oh. God, why?

49:13.875 --> 49:17.277
Do you remember that story that Collin
wrote highlighting the women's clinic

49:17.311 --> 49:19.114
and the services they provide?

49:19.146 --> 49:20.347
Mm-hm.

49:21.981 --> 49:26.621
I added a little bit in there about how
Emeth is protesting them as baby killers,

49:26.653 --> 49:31.492
which is interesting because abortion
isn't even a service they provide.

49:32.693 --> 49:34.562
They didn't like that.

49:34.594 --> 49:37.331
You should report it
to the police.

49:37.364 --> 49:39.366
I did.

49:39.400 --> 49:44.506
They couldn't prove who it was
but it's pretty obvious to me.

49:45.907 --> 49:48.576
They put signs in our yard
the other day.

49:53.914 --> 49:57.684
Apparently, the snide remarks and looks at
the grocery store aren't enough anymore.

49:57.717 --> 50:00.187
And now they are dragging
Arcadia into it.

50:00.221 --> 50:01.556
Oh.

50:01.588 --> 50:03.657
What am I supposed to do,
just ignore it?

50:04.625 --> 50:07.829
How do you fight back
against something like that?

50:07.862 --> 50:13.233
You'll be okay.
You're almost away from them for good.

50:13.266 --> 50:15.369
But you're not.

50:15.402 --> 50:18.205
Yeah, I'd like to really
see them try and fuck with me.

50:20.574 --> 50:22.943
So you got a good
evening planned?

50:22.976 --> 50:25.646
Yeah, Katie's coming over.

50:25.679 --> 50:28.615
I haven't seen her in forever and we're gonna
start planning Arcadia's birthday party.

50:28.648 --> 50:30.217
Oh, sounds fun.

50:30.251 --> 50:31.553
You and Collin
are gonna be there, right?

50:31.585 --> 50:34.321
Wouldn't miss it.
He might, though.

50:34.355 --> 50:36.391
I just... I never know
what's going on with that boy.

50:40.628 --> 50:42.730
- I'll give this to Lisa.
- Thank you.

50:42.762 --> 50:44.465
You're welcome.

50:55.775 --> 50:57.911
How am I gonna run this place
without you?

50:57.945 --> 51:02.884
Hey,
you're gonna kick ass as usual.

51:03.951 --> 51:06.387
- Yeah.
- I'll see you tomorrow.

51:52.365 --> 51:54.969
Hey, it's time for bed, pumpkin.

51:55.001 --> 51:56.570
Can you tell Aunt Katie
good night?

51:56.603 --> 52:00.741
- Good night, Aunt Katie.
- Good night, sweetheart.

52:00.775 --> 52:04.012
Wrap those arms.
Okay, got it.

52:04.045 --> 52:05.713
Okay, let's go.

52:11.018 --> 52:13.420
Oh, no. Uh, what time is it?

52:13.454 --> 52:15.890
Um, I'm so sorry I have to go.

52:15.922 --> 52:19.860
- Uh...
- Okay, bye.

52:29.570 --> 52:30.872
Katie.

52:33.773 --> 52:36.943
Katie. Hey, Katie.

53:07.474 --> 53:10.545
It's his last jab.
Don't get angry. That's what he wants.

53:10.577 --> 53:12.045
They all want you to be upset.

53:12.079 --> 53:16.084
And why shouldn't I be?
It's my fault.

53:17.585 --> 53:19.820
I knew something was off
with Katie.

53:19.853 --> 53:23.523
Ever since her mom died, she's been
drifting further and further away

53:23.556 --> 53:26.794
and I was too busy with you
and Arcadia to be a good friend.

53:28.829 --> 53:31.432
- Fuck.
- It's not your fault.

53:31.465 --> 53:34.902
Her choices aren't your problem.
She's a grown woman.

53:34.934 --> 53:38.539
What matters is that her stupid
decisions don't come back and hurt us.

53:41.608 --> 53:44.378
Yeah, okay.

53:44.411 --> 53:46.513
Mommy?

53:46.547 --> 53:48.516
- You want to take care of that?
- She's calling you, man.

53:50.583 --> 53:52.085
I'll take the next one,
I promise.

53:52.119 --> 53:53.555
Okay.

53:56.856 --> 53:58.893
What is it, baby?

53:58.925 --> 54:04.097
- Do you have a mommy and daddy?
- Yes, but they live far away.

54:04.130 --> 54:07.402
Does daddy have a mommy
and daddy?

54:07.434 --> 54:10.572
- He has a daddy.
- Where is he?

54:14.641 --> 54:17.110
No, absolutely fucking not.

54:17.143 --> 54:19.847
- Just think about it, okay?
- No.

54:20.780 --> 54:25.585
We can't project our issues with your family
on to her, she doesn't know any better.

54:25.619 --> 54:28.823
I mean, we knew this would happen
at some point, we talked about it.

54:28.856 --> 54:32.794
She can meet your family here and then
my family at some point down the road.

54:32.827 --> 54:36.431
Okay, and what if she comes back
and she wants to do Jesus shit?

54:41.068 --> 54:45.473
Then we let her do Jesus shit.
We talked about that too.

54:49.643 --> 54:52.813
Of course, this would happen
as soon as we're about to leave.

54:57.184 --> 54:59.554
Maybe it's for the best.

54:59.586 --> 55:01.855
I can watch her
while we wrap her presents.

